    <title>Matthew J. Tuttle</title>

    
          <script>// Pandoc 2.9 adds attributes on both header and div. We remove the former (to
// be compatible with the behavior of Pandoc < 2.8).
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function(e) {
  var hs = document.querySelectorAll("div.section[class*='level'] > :first-child");
  var i, h, a;
  for (i = 0; i < hs.length; i++) {
    h = hs[i];
    if (!/^h[1-6]$/i.test(h.tagName)) continue;  // it should be a header h1-h6
    a = h.attributes;
    while (a.length > 0) h.removeAttribute(a[0].name);
  }
});
</script>
    
    
  </head>
  <body>

    
    <div class="container-fluid d-none d-lg-block d-xl-block">
      <div class="d-flex row flex-row vh-100">
        <div class="d-flex flex-column col-5 align-items-center text-center align-self-center">
          <div class="mx-auto text-center">
            <div class="p-3">
              <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," style="height:15rem" class="rounded">
            </div>
            <div class="p-2">
              <h1>Matthew J. Tuttle</h1>
            </div>
            <hr style="width:60%;" />
            <div class="p-2">
              <div id="icon-list">
                <ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li class="list-inline-item">
                    <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/mattjtuttle/">
                      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-dark mb-2">
                        LinkedIn
                      </button>
                    </a>
                  </li>
                                    <li class="list-inline-item">
                    <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=xftn0kcAAAAJ">
                      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-dark mb-2">
                        Google Scholar
                      </button>
                    </a>
                  </li>
                                    <li class="list-inline-item">
                    <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4582-2097">
                      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-dark mb-2">
                        ORCID
                      </button>
                    </a>
                  </li>
                                  </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex flex-column vh-100 border-left"></div>
        <div class="d-flex flex-column col px-5 align-items-center align-self-center mh-100" style="overflow-y: scroll;">
          <div class="my-5" id="content">
            <div id="bio" class="section level2">
            <h2>Bio</h2>
            <p>I am a senior research scientist based in the United
            States. Currently, I work at AV Inc. developing technology
            for biomanufacturing of materials. I have expertise in a
            variety of areas including microbiology, synthetic biology,
            environmental sciences, biomanufacturing, and
            bioinformatics.</p>
            <p><br></p>
            </div>
            <div id="experience" class="section level2">
            <h2>Experience</h2>
            <div id="av-inc.-wright-patterson-afb-oh" class="section level5">
            <h5><strong>AV Inc.</strong> | Wright-Patterson AFB, OH</h5>
            <p>Feb 2024 - Present | Senior Scientist, Technical and Team
            Lead</p>
            <p>Jan 2022 - Feb 2024 | Research Scientist</p>
            <p>Jun 2021 - Jan 2022 | Research Consultant</p>
            <p>Feb 2021 - May 2021 | Graduate Research Intern</p>
            <p><br></p>
            </div>
            <div id="american-society-for-microbiology-washington-dc" class="section level5">
            <h5><strong>American Society for Microbiology</strong> |
            Washington, DC</h5>
            <p>Jul 2021 - Jul 2024 | Committee Chair, ASM Young Leaders
            Circle</p>
            <p>Jan 2020 - Dec 2021 | Science Ambassador, Tennessee</p>
